.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-MASQ 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-masq \- masquerading and SNAT rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I masq
file defines masquerading (dynamic SNAT) and static SNAT rules.
Each row tells the compiler to emit a masquerade or snat rule in the
.I inet shorewall
nft table's
.B postrouting
chain.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/masq
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
INTERFACE	yes	Outbound interface (masquerade on this interface)
SOURCE	yes	Source address or CIDR to masquerade
ADDRESS	no	Static SNAT address (empty = dynamic masquerade)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
PORT	no	Destination port filter
IPSEC	no	IPSEC match (ipsec or !ipsec)
MARK	no	Connection mark match
USER	no	User/group match
SWITCH	no	Runtime switch
ORIG_DEST	no	Original destination filter
PROBABILITY	no	Probability for probabilistic SNAT (0.0\(en1.0)
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Masquerade all traffic from the local network on the outbound interface:
.RS
.nf
#INTERFACE  SOURCE
eth0        192.168.1.0/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
Static SNAT to a fixed public IP:
.RS
.nf
eth0        192.168.1.0/24   203.0.113.10
.fi
.RE
.PP
Masquerade only TCP/UDP, leave other protocols unmasqueraded:
.RS
.nf
eth0        10.0.0.0/8       -   tcp
eth0        10.0.0.0/8       -   udp
.fi
.RE

.SH NFSET / DNS TOKENS
The SOURCE column (col 2) accepts
.BR nfset:<name> ,
.BR dns:<hostname> ,
and
.BR dnsr:<hostname>
tokens — see
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)
and
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5)
for the full grammar.
The ADDRESS column (SNAT target) does
.I not
accept these tokens; a literal IP address or CIDR is required there.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-nfsets (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-netmap (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rawnat (5)

